CommonFields.Title: Effects of silane functionalization on the properties of carbon nanotube/epoxy nanocomposites
Author: Ma, Peng Cheng
Kim, Jang-Kyo
Tang, Ben Zhong
CommonFields.Location: Department of Mechanical Engineering, The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology, Clear Water Bay, Kowloon, Hong Kong, PR China

Mixing.Description:
The CNTs were dispersed in ethanol for 1
          h

monomer epoxy was added to the CNT mixture, and the
          mixture was ultrasonicated for 1 h at 80C

ChooseParameter.Other:
The mixture was then outgassed at 80C for 5 h to eliminate the
        entrapped air and the remaining ethanol

Additive.Description:
The m-PDA hardener was added into the mixture in the
          ratio of 14.5:100 by weight

MoldingInfo.Description:
The composite was moulded into a flat plate and cured
            at 80C for 2 h

Heating.Description:
Following moulding, the composite was post cured at
          150C for 2 h

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.Description:
SEM was employed to examine the dispersion states of CNTs
      in the matrix and the fracture morphologies of CNT/epoxy
      nanocomposites

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description:
The samples with dimensions 20 mm long x 3 mm wide x 1 mm
      thick were tested in a three point bending mode from 30 to 170C at a
      heating rate of 10C/min and a frequency of 1.0 Hz within a nitrogen
      atmosphere. The glass transition temperatures, Tg, of nanocomposites
      were also determined from the maxima of the tan-delta acquired from the
      DMA

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description:
Specimens were heated from ambient to 800C at a heating
      rate of 10C/min in the nitrogen flow

Electrometry.Description:
The bulk electrical conductivity of nanocomposites was
      measured at room temperature based on the four-probe method using
      specimens of dimensions 10 mm square x 1 mm in thickness on a
      resistivity/Hall measurement system

ImageFile.Description:
SEM photograph of nanocomposite fracture surface showing
      the dispersion state

SampleSize.description:
mechanical testing samples were 70 mm long x 12.7 mm
        wide
